e blob-code-inner js-file-line\"><span class=\"pl-k\">if</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">__name__</span> <span class=\"pl-k\">==</span> <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">&#39;</span>__main__<span class=\"pl-pds\">&#39;</span></span>:</td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td id=\"file-app-py-L48\" class=\"blob-num js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"48\"></td>\n        <td id=\"file-app-py-LC48\" class=\"blob-code blob-code-inner js-file-line\">    app.run(<span class=\"pl-v\">debug</span><span class=\"pl-k\">=</span><span class=\"pl-c1\">True</span>)</td>\n      </tr>\n</table>\n\n\n  </div>\n\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"gist-meta\">\n        <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/zehengl/7abba6aff362a390a172280b9f8645e8/raw/44c074b05e85b177c3a907d65f92cc4b075c5e75/app.py\" style=\"float:right\">view raw</a>\n        <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/zehengl/7abba6aff362a390a172280b9f8645e8#file-app-py\">app.py</a>\n        hosted with &#10084; by <a href=\"https://github.com\">GitHub</a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n</div></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>python-qrcode does all the dirty work to generate QR code from string</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>flask serves a webapp with only one endpoint, it returns the form upon GET and displays the QR code image upon POST</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"http://flask.pocoo.org/snippets/32/\">the flask snippet</a> shows how to avoid creating a temp file for the image</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>The Deploy</h2>\n<p>Deploying this simple MVP to Heroku is easy.</p>\n<h3>requirements.txt</h3>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">pip freeze</code> the dependencies to a requirements.txt file</p>\n<h3>Procfile</h3>\n<p>Create a Procfile to declare it as a web app served by gunicorn <code class=\"language-text\">web: gunicorn app:app --log-file=-</code></p>\n<p>See <a href=\"https://devcenter.heroku.com/articles/getting-started-with-python#introduction\">Getting Started on Heroku with Python</a> for more info.</p>","frontmatter":{"t